Package: mc-daemon
Version: 0.9.0
Section: net
Priority: optional
Architecture: ARCHITECTURE_PLACEHOLDER
Maintainer: Wilderness Labs <support@wildernesslabs.co>
Depends: systemd, openssh-client
Description: Meadow Daemon - Linux service for OTA updates and Meadow.Cloud connectivity
 Meadow.Daemon is a Rust-based service that provides client connectivity and
 Over-The-Air (OTA) update functionality for applications in the Meadow ecosystem.
 .
 Features:
  - REST API on port 5000 for application interaction
  - MQTT-based cloud connectivity for update notifications
  - Secure authentication with Meadow.Cloud using RSA/AES encryption
  - Local update management and application
  - Systemd service integration
Homepage: https://github.com/WildernessLabs/Meadow.Daemon
